[src:actor-critic/markov-decision-process] When this assumption is not true, the problem is called a partially observable Markov decision process or POMDP.
[src:actor-critic/markov-decision-process] Constrained Markov decision processes (CMDPS) are extensions to Markov decision process (MDPs).
[src:actor-critic/markov-decision-process] There are three fundamental differences between MDPs and CMDPs.
[src:actor-critic/markov-decision-process] The method of Lagrange multipliers applies to CMDPs.
